    <tags>react, fluent-ui, frontend, shared-components</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Authors a Fluent v9 React component in the shared library (`@spaarke/ui-components`); tags include `react`, `fluent-ui`, and `frontend`; ADR-021 (Fluent v9 tokens, dark mode) is binding; design.md §6.0 mandates `/fluent-v9-component` invocation for any Fluent v9 component authoring task.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-SC-01, add a generic multi-select chip filter component `TagFilter` to `@spaarke/ui-components`. The component is NOT bound to document type — it is reusable for any choice field. Its first consumer (later task) is the Semantic Search PCF Tags filter (FR-DOC-05), but the component itself must be choice-field-agnostic. Props: `{ options: TagFilterOption[], selected: string[], onChange: (selected: string[]) =&gt; void, label?: string, sortAlphabetical?: boolean }`. Renders Fluent v9 `Menu` + `MenuItemCheckbox`; trigger button shows label + count badge; below-bar active-tags chip row appears when ≥1 selected; chip × removes single tag; "Clear all" empties selection. Component MUST use Fluent v9 semantic tokens only (zero hardcoded hex/rgb), render correctly in dark mode (NFR-04), and remain compatible with React 16/17 (PCF platform, ADR-022).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend developer with deep Fluent UI v9 experience (Menu, MenuItemCheckbox, Tag, Badge, makeStyles + tokens) and familiarity with `@spaarke/ui-components` barrel-export conventions. Comfortable authoring generic, framework-style components that ship with TypeScript types and zero coupling to specific Dataverse entities or PCF host plumbing.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A reusable, choice-field-agnostic Fluent v9 multi-select chip filter exported from `@spaarke/ui-components` as `TagFilter`, with companion type `TagFilterOption` exported alongside. The shared library builds clean (`npm run build:prod`). Both PCFs (Semantic Search + Visual Host) still build against the updated shared library. The component passes axe in light and dark; multi-select OR semantics work; chip × removes a single tag; "Clear all" empties selection.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-SC-01 specifies a generic Tags filter component because the spec explicitly forbids parallel implementations and the same UX is expected to be reused beyond document types in future work. ADR-012 places the component in `@spaarke/ui-components`. ADR-021 binds Fluent v9 tokens + dark-mode parity. The Semantic Search PCF (a later task) will be the first consumer — its Tags filter is the relocated existing Document Type filter from the sidebar `FilterPanel`. Building this component first unblocks task 012 (barrel update) and downstream Semantic Search PCF work (FR-DOC-05).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/TagFilter.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/TagFilter.ts</file>
