    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 component authoring" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md">
        Use `makeStyles` + `tokens` for all styling; never hardcode color/spacing values; expose typed props.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 theming + dark mode" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-theming.md">
        Token-only rule; verify both webLightTheme and webDarkTheme during dev.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Shared barrel export" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts">
        Re-export both the component and its public types from the barrel; component-first ordering within the section.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check">Verify context &lt; 60%. If higher, run `context-handoff` before proceeding.</step>
    <step order="0.5" name="Invoke fluent-v9-component">Invoke `Skill fluent-v9-component` (binding per design.md §6.0). Load patterns (`fluent-v9-component-authoring.md`, `fluent-v9-theming.md`, `fluent-v9-react-version-boundaries.md`) and skill guidance before reading any Fluent v9 component file.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Load knowledge">Read ADR-012, ADR-021, ADR-022, and the three ui patterns above. Read existing `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts` to confirm barrel conventions. Confirm `@fluentui/react-components` is already a dependency.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Define types">Create `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/TagFilter.ts` exporting `TagFilterOption { value: string; label: string; }` and `TagFilterProps { options: TagFilterOption[]; selected: string[]; onChange: (selected: string[]) =&gt; void; label?: string; sortAlphabetical?: boolean; }`.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement component">Create `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/TagFilter.tsx` rendering: (a) Fluent v9 `Menu` trigger button with label + count badge (e.g., `Tags (2)` when 2 selected); (b) `MenuPopover` containing `MenuList` of `MenuItemCheckbox` entries, one per option, optionally alphabetically sorted by `label` when `sortAlphabetical` is true; (c) below-bar chip row using Fluent v9 `Tag` components (or `InteractionTag` with dismiss action) rendered ONLY when `selected.length &gt;= 1`; each chip's × calls `onChange(selected.filter(s =&gt; s !== chipValue))`; (d) a "Clear all" subtle button at the end of the chip row that calls `onChange([])`. Use `makeStyles` + `tokens` exclusively — verify zero hex/rgb.</step>
    <step order="4" name="A11y + dark mode">Verify roles/labels: the trigger button has `aria-label` derived from `label` prop; the chip × buttons have `aria-label="Remove {label}"`. Render component in dev harness with both `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme` (FluentProvider wrap) and confirm contrast + token resolution.</step>
    <step order="5" name="React 16/17 compatibility">Confirm no React 18+ exclusive APIs are imported (no `use()`, no `useId` from React 18 — use Fluent's `useId` from `@fluentui/react-components` if needed). Confirm `package.json` peerDependencies allow React ^16 || ^17 (it already does, but verify no new types reference React 18 features).</step>
    <step order="6" name="Build verification">From `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components`, run `npm run build:prod`. Then from each consuming PCF (`src/client/pcf/SemanticSearchControl`, `src/client/pcf/VisualHost`), run `npm run build:prod` to confirm the shared library still compiles end-to-end. Note: barrel export of `TagFilter` itself is deferred to task 012 — this step only verifies the shared library and PCF builds succeed with the new file present but unexported.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Self-review">Re-read the component file: confirm no hardcoded colors, no Matter-specific code paths, no document-type-specific imports, no console.log, no dead code, no `any` types.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Checkpoint">Run `context-handoff` (silent: ✅ Checkpoint).</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">Invoke `Skill code-review` then `Skill adr-check`. Resolve every finding before completion. The code-review skill specifically enforces `/fluent-v9-component` was invoked at Step 0.5 — if skipped, the merge is blocked.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Update task tracking">Update `projects/spaarke-matter-ui-enhancement-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: task 010 status 🔲 → ✅. Reset `projects/spaarke-matter-ui-enhancement-r1/current-task.md` to the next pending task (likely 011).</step>
  </steps>

